<br>
As to locking the cockpit, with a significant barrier, without guns... it has advantages and disadvantages.<br>
<br>
Disadvantages:  Higher plane weight, meaning less fuel efficiency and thus higher cost to the airlines.  In addition, planes take money to re-design.  Also, it doesn't protect the passengers... they're still hostages in a terrorist situation.  If the pilot has a gun, the door can seal the pilot in as well as keep bad guys out, so he's useless, and if he comes out his gun can be stolen.<br>
<br>
Advantages:  Keeps certain people out of the cockpit.<br>
<br>
I dunno if it's worth it... I can idly think of ways to bypass such a door (such as lure the pilot out with one person, then jump them with another).<br>
