<br>
When I served as a cross country chaser in the Marine Corps I carried my side arm on every civilian flight I took.<br>
<br>
Other law enforcment folks also carry them. So, guns are allready on flights and a terrorist knowing that could get it.<br>
<br>
<br>
But, that being said I don't believe the pilots having a fire arm is a particularly good move. They are pilots, not law enforcement. They fly planes, that is their job.<br>
<br>
If the weapon was to remain in the cockpit at all times and only to be used to defend against forced entry into the cockpit I might be more inclined to think it was somewhat acceptable, but even then I wouldn't like the idea.<br>
<br>
As far as the &quot;Captain Jesse James&quot; and going ballistic thats just sensationalistic crap.<br>
<br>
